            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><h3><span>Father’s Day Car Show</span></h3>
<p>Sunday, June 15 from 10 am to 3 pm<br>
Cost:&nbsp;Single - $8.67; Family (Up to two adults, and accompanying children, all living in the same household) - $22.49</p>
<p>Treat your dad, paternal role model, or favourite car enthusiast to a day of family-friendly fun at Billings Estate National Historic Site. Chat with community members about their pre-1999 antique and vintage cars. The Billings’ 1959 Cadillac Sedan de Ville will also be on display. Visitors can cast a vote for their favourite car, explore the museum at Ottawa’s oldest wood frame house, and challenge each other to a scavenger hunt.</p>
<h4><span>Register to participate in the show with your vehicle</span></h4>
<p>Car owners are invited to participate in the Father’s Day Car Show at Billings Estate National Historic Site with their pre-1999 vehicles (no ‘mods’ or hotrods). To participate, please complete the <a href="https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=PQPM34ffbkyhuI6qc_G3LkahVhqR9VBKtBvkVM-3DjxUNUNIMkFUMVEwRFpBQjUxTlM1NUdFVFNEMSQlQCN0PWcu">online registration form</a> by June 11, 2025.</p>
<p>Please plan to arrive at the museum (2100 Cabot Street) on June 15 between 8:30 am and 9:45 pm. We hope that you will be able to participate for the duration of the event. If you need to depart early, we request that you depart on the hour so we can coordinate the movement of vehicles. Registered car owners will receive two chits for lunch.</p>
<p>If you have questions, contact <a href="mailto:larysa.voss@ottawa.ca">larysa.voss@ottawa.ca</a></p>
<h4><strong>Notes</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>This program takes place rain or shine. Please dress for weather conditions, including proper footwear for uneven, grassy, or gravel terrain.</li>
<li>As many of the vehicles are owned by community members, the number of participating vehicles may vary throughout the day (or be impacted by inclement weather).</li>
<li>If you have questions or concerns regarding accessibility, please contact the museum at 613-580-2088 or by email at <a href="mailto:museums@ottawa.ca">museums@ottawa.ca</a>. Additional <a href="https://ottawa.ca/en/node/1007407/">information about accessibility</a> can be found on the museum webpage.</li>
</ul>
